The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning for object recognition tasks using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for this task, which is a popular area of research in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm involves training a CNN without labeled data, which is a common theme in unsupervised learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm on well-known datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
